title: Drawing, "A Warehouse of the 16th Century in Pisa, Italy", October 7, 1890
medium: Graphite, brush and watercolor on paper
inscribed: Inscribed in graphite, above: Echelle 0.002 = M. 1 / Date on coat of arms, 1588 / Probably the 3 yellow ones were done earlier. Lower: Entrepot à Pisa / October 7th 1890 / (Used for artillery stables)
description: Above, elevation of a slightly, obliquely disposed one-story building of eight bays, five of which contain doors; center, elevation of two of the brick bays; a pedestal with the coat of arms of the Medici rises over a pilaster at left; scale below; lower section, a plan of wall beside a door and a part of the plan of the building.

tombstone.epitaph:
Drawing, "A Warehouse of the 16th Century in Pisa, Italy", October 7, 1890.
October 7, 1890. Graphite, brush and watercolor on paper. Gift of Mrs. William Greenough. 1943-51-9.
